    "department": "Data",
    "description": "ABOUT ONEPAY\n\nOnePay is the consumer fintech trusted by millions of Americans to make money better.\n\nOur financial system is broken. High fees, low rates, and too few ways to actually grow your money. We’re fixing it. And we’re moving fast.\n\nWe’re an all-in-one financial services platform that brings together banking, high-yield savings, credit cards, point-of-sale lending, investing, and crypto in one place. We also partner with employers, HCM providers, gig platforms, and others to deliver embedded financial services to millions of employees and frontline workers.\n\nWe’re backed by Walmart, the world’s largest retailer, and Ribbit Capital, one of fintech’s most respected investors, giving us rare scale, distribution, and the opportunity to build something truly category-defining.\n\nBut what really sets OnePay apart is how we move. Our customers don’t have time to wait… and neither do we. This place moves fast, and we’re looking for people who are:\n\n - Ready to run\n\n - Hungry and driven by urgency\n\n - Exceptional at what they do, with low ego\n\n - Comfortable operating in motion\n\n\nTHE ROLE\n\nIn this Paid Media Analytics role your mandate will be to drive data driven decisions in our Paid Media strategies across search, social, affiliates and other paid media platforms.  You’ll play a critical role in helping us optimize our media investments, improve our customer acquisition efficiency, and drive smarter decision-making with data. You will have the opportunity to work alongside amazing teams such as our Growth Marketing, Analytics Engineering and Finance.\n\nThis role is responsible for:\n\n - Analyzing performance across all paid marketing channels (search, social, affiliates), focusing on down-funnel metrics such as CAC, ROAS, and conversion quality to optimize our investment decisions.\n\n - Identifying actionable insights and partnering with our Growth Marketing team to continuously optimize spend and targeting.\n\n - Design and lead a wide ranging testing agenda, including geo-lift tests and holdouts, to better understand the true impact of upper-funnel investments.\n\n - Build and maintain predictive models to power advanced bidding strategies, including Value-Based Bidding (VBB) and projected ROAS frameworks.\n\n\nYOU BRING\n\n - 5+ years in Paid Media or marketing analytics roles\n\n - MUST HAVE APP INSTALL CAMPAIGN EXPERIENCE (i.e. Google UAC / Apple Search Ads / Meta App Install etc)\n\n - Experience working in an analytical scripting language (primarily SQL) is a must with concrete understanding of common statistical methods and experimentation, with strong focus on incrementality testing. Experience with platforms such as GA4 a plus, but the core requirement of this role is advanced SQL experience\n\n - Preferred channel experience includes UAC/ASA, Paid Social (Meta Ads / TikTok), Paid Search, Google Ads \n   \n   - OLV/Streaming Audio \u0026 Affiliates experience is a plus\n\n - Strong written and verbal skills - inclusive of the ability to distill technical subjects for non-technical audiences and effectively communicate findings to stakeholders and executive leadership.\n\n - Strong drive and sense of ownership to autonomously drive analysis and projects.\n\n\nWHAT WE OFFER\n\n - Competitive base salary, stock options, and health benefits from Day 1\n\n - 401(k) plan with company match\n\n - Remote-friendly (US), flexible time off (FTO), and opportunities for growth\n\n - A high-growth, mission-driven, inclusive culture where your work has real impact.\n\n\nSTANDARD INTERVIEW PROCESS\n\n - Initial Interview with Talent Partner\n\n - Technical or Hiring Manager Interview\n\n - Team Interview\n\n - Executive Interview\n\n - Offer!\n\n\nEQUAL EMPLOYMENT OPPORTUNITY\n\nTo build technology and products that are used and loved by people and solve real-world problems, we need to build a team with many different perspectives and experiences. We are an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. We encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply. Applicants in need of special assistance or accommodation during the interview process or in accessing our website may contact us at talent@onepay.com.",
